==Literary references==
As with ''[[Steel (Battle Beast album)|Steel]]'', several songs on ''Battle Beast'' reference the [[dark fantasy]] [[manga]] ''[[Berserk (manga)|Berserk]]'' by [[Kentaro Miura]]: "Out of Control", "Golden Age", "Kingdom", and "Fight, Kill, Die". "Neuromancer", meanwhile, is about the [[William Gibson]] [[cyberpunk]] [[novel]] of [[Neuromancer|same name]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://metaldivas.wordpress.com/2013/06/10/interview-noora-louhimo-battle-beast/ |title=INTERVIEW: Noora Louhimo (Battle Beast) |date=10 June 2013 |website=Metal Divas |publisher=[[WordPress.com]] |access-date=22 May 2017}}</ref>

==Personnel==
===Battle Beast===
*Noora Louhimo - [[Lead vocalist|lead vocals]]
*Anton Kabanen - [[lead guitar]], [[Backing vocalist|backing vocals]], production, engineering, mixing
*Juuso Soinio - [[rhythm guitar]]
*Eero Sipilä - [[Bass guitar|bass]], backing vocals
*Pyry Vikki - [[Drum kit|drums]]
*Janne Björkroth - [[Keyboard instrument|keyboard]]s, orchestration, backing vocals, co-production, engineering, mixing

===Additional musicians===
*Joonas Kaikko - [[Percussion instrument|percussion]]

===Production===
*Lucas Lönnross - engineer
*Mika Jussila - mastering at [[Finnvox Studios]]

